<br>
&lt;b&gt;Hymn to Forever&lt;/b&gt;<br>
Fire transpires from funeral pires, smoke tall as spires, echoes from choirs, a mans time expired.  I cried cause he died, and his life brushed aside, and denied, god please guide him into forever the final endeavor however please never sever the ties between us though I scream and I cus and I curse you and fus, please forgive me....<br>
<br>
wow... that was wierd, especially cause I dont usually write rhyming poems... anyways moving on...<br>
<br>
&lt;b&gt;Rejection&lt;/b&gt;<br>
I arrive at a door, theres something on the other side, something I yearn for, when I walk up to the door it strikes me in the face sending me down into the floor, leaving me with a sore ass and a longing to know what is on the other side.<br>
<br>
::tear, tear::<br>
<br>
Screaming within me the answer to all of my questions is tearing away at my insides and ripping me to peices because it knows and I do not and it tries to get out in word but i can't breathe and it is lodged in my throat and i scream and the answer is thrown into the wind muffled by my own shout and i never hear it see it or feel it again.<br>
<br>
this was entirely freewritten from inspiration like right now, which is why it lacks punctuation and such, but im not fixing it... i like it in its unadulturated state.<br>
<br>
Tell me what you all think and dont comment on form because i was avoiding form on purpose<br>
<br>
